# Freshservice CLI

A command-line tool for managing Freshservice tickets.

## Features

- List tickets with optional filters (status, priority)
- View detailed ticket information
- Update ticket status

## Installation

This project uses `uv` for dependency management. After cloning the repository:

```bash
uv sync
```

## Configuration

Set your Freshservice API key as an environment variable:

```bash
export FRESHSERVICE_API_KEY="your-api-key"
export FRESHSERVICE_DOMAIN="your-domain.freshservice.com"
```

You can also use a `.env` file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your credentials
```

## Usage

```bash
# List all tickets
fresh-cli list

# List tickets with filters
fresh-cli list --status open --priority 1 --limit 10

# View a specific ticket
fresh-cli view 123

# Update ticket status
fresh-cli status 123 resolved
```

## Available Commands

- `list` - List tickets with optional filters
  - `--status` - Filter by status (open, pending, resolved, closed)
  - `--priority` - Filter by priority (1-4)
  - `--limit` - Maximum number of tickets to show (default: 20)

- `view <ticket_id>` - View detailed ticket information

- `status <ticket_id> <status>` - Update ticket status
  - Status values: open, pending, resolved, closed

## API Status Values

- 2 = Open
- 3 = Pending
- 4 = Resolved
- 5 = Closed
```

